data.content:
Three breaking changes hit your code. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes `Func<>`, not `Expression<Func<>>`

Your manual expression tree building **won't compile** anymore. The good news: it's now *much* simpler.

```csharp
// EF Core 10 — regular lambda with imperative logic
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

Delete all the `Expression.Lambda`, `Expression.Call`, `Expression.Parameter` machinery.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — now auto-uniquified & nested paths changed

**Two changes at once:**

- **Uniquification:** `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously silently shared one `Street` column (data corruption risk). Now EF appends a number (`Street`, `Street1`). This **will generate a migration that renames columns**.
- **Nested full path:** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was previously `BillingAddress_City`, now becomes `Payment_BillingAddress_City`.

To keep existing column names and avoid a breaking migration:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});

// For nested complex types, pin the old name:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gains a `string logCommandText` parameter (contains redacted SQL for safe logging):

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (sensitive data redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual execution SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
